result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defense Counsel request to remove Shannon M. from the WRITTEN NO CONTACT ORDER is GRANTED at this time.  Shannon M. present during these proceedings and has consented to same.

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed and read-in to case 13CF4164 and 13CM3941 for the purposes of sentencing.
Defense petitioned the Court for removal of Written No Contact Order as to Shannon M.  Shannon M.  present during these proceedings and has ORALLY PRESENTED HER CONSENT to the Court for the removal of the WRITTEN NO CONTACT ORDER at this time.

Attorney William F Sulton in court, defendant Austin Leroy Lynn not in court, in custody.  Thomas L Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Bail motion by defense argued and granted by the Court.  Bail adjusted down to $500.00 CASH BAIL with previous terms and conditions set remaining in place.  Plea Hearing previously scheduled for 03-12-2014 remains on Court's Calendar.
Call received from Attorney William Sulton to schedule Bail Bond Motion Hearing.  Bail Motion Hearing scheduled for 02-24-2014 at 08:30am in Branch 22.
For A Reduction In Bail By Austin Leroy Lynn, FILED.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.
Defense Counsel request to remove Shannon M. from the WRITTEN NO CONTACT ORDER is denied at this time.

Defendant Austin Leroy Lynn in court with attorney William F Sulton.  Defendant Austin Leroy Lynn in custody.  Michael Lonski for Thomas L Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
 Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed.  Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Witkowiak, Branch 22.  Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty.  Plea hearing scheduled for March 12, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision and Electronic Monitoring.  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY  to be monitored by drug testing and portable breathalyzers.
  Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Shannon M. and family.

Defendant Austin Leroy Lynn in court with attorney William F Sulton.  Defendant Austin Leroy Lynn in custody.  Carole R Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Witkowiak, Branch 22.  
Defense motion to dismiss for lack of probable caue is heard, argued by the State and DENIED by the Court.
Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings. Defendant enters a plea of not guilty as to misdemeanor count 1.
Defendant has court appointed counsel.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for February 7, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
